.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-SCHEMA" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.47" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-schema \- Print the hpc\-compose JSON Schema
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose schema [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Print the checked\-in JSON Schema for compose authoring tools (default) or settings.toml authoring tools (\-\-kind settings). Rust validation remains the semantic source of truth.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--kind\fR \fIKIND\fR
Which schema to print: 'compose' (default) or 'settings'. Possible values: compose, settings.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose schema
hpc\-compose schema > hpc\-compose.schema.json
.fi
